<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85243"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> ...tick...<br />
<br />
...tock...<br />
<br />
...tick...<br />
<br />
...tock...<br />
<br />
....ticktockticktockticktockTICKTOCK...<br />
<br />
"I hate Ak'Anon." Vven murmured in disgust.<br />
<br />
"So do I, brother, so do I." Riverdane agreed, squatting on his haunches in front of the small house, knocking hard on the door.<br />
<br />
Ak'Anon. Steamfront Mountains. Home of the gnomes, gnarled men, cute petite women, eternal tinkerers, gadget makers, masters of the lever and spring, creaters of clocks and modern tools. And all through the land, that persistant, maddening noise. Tick TOCK.<br />
<br />
No answer.<br />
<br />
"Must be all this noise." River remarked. "It's amazing gnomes can hear anything at all."<br />
<br />
"It's because you are human!" Vven snorted, rolling up his sleeve. "Learn to knock with authority!". He rapped his knuckle against the door with a hrumph.<br />
<br />
And through it.<br />
<br />
"Hmm." Vven remarked, a little out of sorts. "I passed my hand through, as if discorpreal." River just looked at him, and where his arm ended with the wrist flush against the door, hand passing through it as if the door didn't exist.<br />
<br />
"I imagine, you being dead has something to do with that." River commented, watching Vven draw his hand from the door.<br />
<br />
"Lovely. I am a ghost." Vven said with disgust. "That should prove cumbersome."<br />
<br />
River knocked again. "Whizbang, you old goat, let me in!"<br />
<br />
Whether it be his shout or the occupants finally hearing the knock, the small door opened without a creak. Good old fashion Gnome Oil made sure of that.<br />
<br />
There in the framework of the miniature door, stood a tiny gnome woman with a rolling pin in one hand. Her eyes smiled when she saw River.<br />
<br />
"Well well, Riverdane Wyldechylde, I haven't seen you in ages!" she exclaimed.<br />
<br />
"Hello Ms. Dustyboots." River said with a smile. The smell of some confection permeated the air. River may not need to eat, but the smell of good cooking still gave his senses a turn for the better.<br />
<br />
"Call me Pedi, boy, or don't come calling at all!" she exclaimed. "You know better than that! And who is this with you? Oh.." Now taking a close look at Vven. "A dark elf. How...lovely. Well well come in, come in. I imagine the smell of my cooking isn't what brought you here."<br />
<br />
Vven looked at the tiny door with an eyebrow raised. "And how, madam, do you expect us to fit into this quaint little....doll house?"<br />
<br />
But Pedi was already anticipating the question. She handed them both small vials. "Just drink up and come in." she said. River took the small vial from her. Vven tried to, but it passed through his hand and shattered on the ground.<br />
<br />
"Oh...my." she said, staring at the puddle on the ground. "Perfectly good waste of a shrink potion. You do have a little problem, don't you, young man? Well, I'm afraid then you'll have to crawl in...."<br />
<br />
River had already partaken in the contents of the vial, and was slowly changing form, shrinking down to Pedi's small stature.<br />
<br />
"The hells I will crawl through the home of a gnome!" Vven snorted. "May Innoruuk forgive me." he murmured, reciting an incantation. And with a shimmer, his image changed to a small gnome, white beard and all. But he kept his bright blue skin. The effect was....disquieting.<br />
<br />
"My, you look just like a..." Pedi began.<br />
<br />
"Shall we proceed?" Vven interrupted, pushing into the house.<br />
<br />
"Your friend needs to learn to be polite!" Pedi commented to River as he looked at her apologetically.<br />
<br />
"That WAS him polite." River said, entering the house and closing the door behind him. <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***    ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
"WHIZBANG YOU HAVE VISITORS!"<br />
<br />
Riverdane shook his head in a daze as the echoes of Pedi's shout reverberated through the house. For such a petite woman she certainly could give the bards a run for volume.<br />
<br />
A voice came from the doorway leading into the basement.<br />
<br />
"Visitors? So soon? Blast them, they're early! I didn't expect the new guild applicants till noon!" A crash of a chest being closed, then some more noise, something falling to the floor, followed by a lot of somethings falling to the floor, a string of colorful gnomish curses, and small feet pounding up wooden stairs.<br />
<br />
And that was just the beginning of his entrance.<br />
<br />
"I am Whizbang Dustyboots, gnomish sorcerer of the third rank, Baron of the Dragonscale Hills and wielder of the Staff of the Four! I am the scourge of the Teir'Dal, death incarnate to the Kromzek and ..." Whizbang stopped mid-sentence, scratching his white goatee and looking at River and Vven.<br />
<br />
"I know." River smiled.<br />
<br />
"I don't, go on." Vven interjected. "Specially the scum of the Teir'Dal..."<br />
<br />
"Scourge, my blue tainted cousin, scourge." Whizbang replied, peering at Vven. "I must say, your pigmentation I have never seen before on a gnome. Although, I must have record of it somewhere in this house. No matter, I will find it after our business here is conducted. But yes, many a Teir'Dal has tasted the wrathe of my fire. If I had my way, I would enter Neriak itself and lay wast..."<br />
<br />
"Whizbang..." Pedi tried to cut in, but he shushed her with a wave of his hand.<br />
<br />
"...lay waste to the twisted children of Innoruuk. Their sole purposes seem to be..."<br />
<br />
Pedi seemed more urgent. "Whizbang, our guest is...." she tried again.<br />
<br />
"Damnation, woman, WHAT?" Whizbang cried in frustration.<br />
<br />
She glared at him. "Our guest is..."<br />
<br />
"An inky." Vven supplied, with a crooked grin. <br />
<br />
"Whizbang, meet Vven. An old aquaintance of mine." River offered. "He was a Teir'Dal enchanter in life, thus this little illusion to enter your house."<br />
<br />
"Hrummph." Whizbang hrummphed, "Blue skin. A mockery of gnomes in my house. Well, River, you've got my attention." Then something dawned on him. "You say '...was a Teir'Dal enchanter in life' Was. What is the meaning of that, does he not live now?"<br />
<br />
"I'm sorta dead, gnome." Vven answered. "I'm not just blue because I'm a Teir'Dal. I'm blue cause I'm not breathing."<br />
<br />
Whizbang looked at River for a sign of a joke, and was more disturbed by the serious look on his old friends' face.<br />
<br />
"We need to talk about this....and more, don't we, River." Whiz said. It was not a question.<br />
<br />
"Yes, and more." River replied.<br />
<br />
"To my basement. We will have privacy there." Whiz said, ushering them though the doorway to the staircase that led into his library. "Pedi, please bring some refreshment, and join us."<br />
<br />
"Oh good," Pedi replied. "I just made a fresh batch of Gnome Shaped Cookies..."<br />
<br />
"Damnation, woman!" Whizbang exploded. "How many times do I have to tell you no Gnome Shape Cookies in this house! It's symbolic of cannibalism, I tell you, and I won't...."<br />
<br />
"YOU'LL EAT THEM AND LIKE THEM!" Pedi roared. River nearly tripped down the stairs. Whizbang's mouth snapped shut and he descended into the cool depths of the library. Pedi turned a warm smile on her still youthful face towards River.<br />
<br />
"Now, watch your footing, gentlemen, and you can tell us all about it down below. Have a cookie?"  <br /></font></p>
	
