<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85244"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> ...inhale...<br />
<br />
"You say Innoruuk is dead." Whizbang said after a pause. The two gnomes and River sat at an oak table, with a burning candle and platter of cookies on it, while Vven paced nervously around the room, glancing at the hundreds of titles of Whizbang's library.<br />
<br />
"Dead." River replied, watching Whizbang's face for any sign of belief. Whizbang was impossible to read when lost in thought, and lost in thought he seemed. "Or...gone at least. Done in, in some way. The Elite acknowledged me as their new master."<br />
<br />
Pedi's face was distraught. "Poor poor Camille! Trapped in Hate. River, how could you have made that agreement with Innoruuk? Any of us could have told you she gave you her soul long ag..." But she trailed off unfinished, as River turned to her with a look of such self loathing she was left speechless.<br />
<br />
"I know." he said softly.<br />
<br />
She patted his hand. "Well, it is the curse of all things male to make at least one huge mistake in their lives." she said. "Now it is time to fix it."<br />
<br />
"And fix ME, River." Vven said from behind him. "An eternity playing spook for a human is not my destiny. Not even Innoruuk had that cruel a sense of humor!"<br />
<br />
"I'm WORKING on it." River replied testily. He turned back to Whizbang. "So, Whiz, any advice? Do you even believe me?"<br />
<br />
"You've never lied to me before, to my knowledge, River, and I don't expect you would concoct something this bizarre even as a joke. Plus no one would suffer the ravings of this dark elf," a gesture to Vven, met with a theatrical hiss from the enchanter, "for no reason. So yes, I believe you. Do I know how to proceed? No. My mind is old, but something keeps dancing at the edge of it. Something important. Something I've read." His eyes got a very faraway look in the candlelight. "What was it......what was it.....something you said tripped a switch...."<br />
<br />
Suddenly his eyes focused in again. "Yes! That's it. Camille. You had said you had at first thought when she drowned herself she was with Marr. Mithaniel Marr, not Erollsi, yes? Camille worshipped Mithaniel?"<br />
<br />
"Aye, Whiz. How did you guess that? Most women worshipped Erollsi rather than Mithaniel, but Camille was different. She called Erollsi too soft for a woman of steel. How did you guess that..."<br />
<br />
"Because it makes sense. It is all starting to make sense." Whizbang replied. But rather than look happy with his discovery, Whizbang's look became more and more worried, deep lines cutting into his forehead.<br />
<br />
"River," he said suddenly. "You say you haven't eaten or taken drink in almost a week, yet have suffered no desire or need for food or water? A result of your godhood? And you were able to will yourself to my doorstep from Hate, correct?"<br />
<br />
"Yes." River replied, "I haven't felt the need to eat or sleep or drink or...."<br />
<br />
And before River could even react, Whizbang with quick movements pulled a long hair pin from Pedi's bun, and drove it into River's palm. <br />
<br />
"What the OWWW DAMMIT!" River cried as the pin drove itself in and through his palm. Whiz pulled the pin out and absently handed it to a shocked Pedi, staring at River's twitching palm. At first there was nothing, but then the blood began to flow, puddling in River's palm and dripping to the table. River glared at Whizbang, teeth gritted in pain.<br />
<br />
"Hells, and you call the Teir'Dal sadists...", Vven chuckled.<br />
<br />
"You are mortal yet." Whizbang murmured. "Pedi, your skills please." <br />
<br />
Pedi took River's palm into her hands and closed her eyes. From under her lids, a flash of blue light. And then, the pain was gone, the wound disappearing before River's eyes. He knew Pedi was a cleric of no meager skills, but the shock of what Whiz had done still left him rattled.<br />
<br />
"Whiz, what in the gods' names was that all about?" River asked, accepting a handtowel Pedi handed to him to clean up the blood. She then swatted Whizbang hard on the head.<br />
<br />
"STOP stabbing the guests!" she warned.<br />
<br />
"Damnation woman!" Whizbang cried, rubbing the lump that began forming on his forehead. "I needed to know for certain!"<br />
<br />
"Know WHAT, Whiz?" River asked.<br />
<br />
"If you were still mortal. A god yet still mortal." Whizbang said, leaping up, starting to peer at books lining his walls. "Mortal Hate. I needed to know....." A pause, two books pushed aside, more frantic searching. "Where is it, where is it...?.....I needed to know if you were mortal Hate...damnation, where is my Lexicon Of Prophecy??"<br />
<br />
Pedi and Vven pointed at the same time about a foot to Whizbang's left, and uttered the same word.<br />
<br />
"There.", they said.<br />
<br />
"Hrrumph." Whiz hrrumphed, pulling it off the shelf. Dust flew as he did. He slapped it down flat on the table in such a rush that he forgot River's puddle of blood, and the blood spread out from around the book's edges like a crimson aura. Whizbang began flipping through the pages in a rush.<br />
<br />
"So this book has the answer to my problem?" River asked, trying to make out any of the words or runes that flipped by as Whiz tore through the pages.<br />
<br />
"I'm afraid this is much bigger than your friend Vven's life, or Camille's or your own, River." Whiz said distractedly, still searching through the book.<br />
<br />
River's bloody hand clamped over Whiz's, stopping the gnome for a moment. <br />
<br />
"What do you mean?" River asked intensely.<br />
<br />
"My boy," Whiz said, turning to look at River dead in the eyes. "If I am not mistaken, what you have described to me with be the end of Norrath. Of all things living...and dead."<br />
<br />
Vven leaned in close. "Wizard do you mean..."<br />
<br />
"End Game." Whizbang whispered. <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
...a held breath...<br />
<br />
"End Game?" River asked blankly.<br />
<br />
"Yes, End Game." Whizbang replied, turning back to his book. "End Game is..."<br />
<br />
"...the end of everything." Vven finished for him. "The Apocolypse. The destruction of everything. Everything just ceasing to be. Even we follower of Hate feared the thought of End Game."<br />
<br />
Whiz continue on, flipping pages frantically as River digested what he was hearing. "End Game, called thus on the latter day belief that we are just pawns being shuffled by a higher intelligence, beings greater than we, somehow more real than even the gods themselves. An absurd theory, if you ask me, but an apt enough name. End Game. The end of all games, this game that is our existance. There is a prophecy tied into End Game, and an odd one at that. Now where the Hells is it?"<br />
<br />
---Flip---<br />
<br />
"...You see, the prophecy itself is unique, in a very odd way, which lends it some notice, if not full credibility..."<br />
<br />
---Flip---<br />
<br />
"This version is in Common Tongue, but I, a master linguist, noticed something very odd about it..."<br />
<br />
---Flip---<br />
<br />
"It rhymes, not very cleverly, but it holds to a certain rhyming pattern. As most prophecies do....that was not the oddity..."<br />
<br />
---Flip---<br />
<br />
---flipflip---<br />
<br />
"But regardless of what language it is translated into, whether it the grunts of the Trollish folk, the lyrical language of the High Elves, the gutteral slang of the Teir'Dal, regardless of the language..."<br />
<br />
---flip---<br />
<br />
"It STILL rhymes."<br />
<br />
River looked at Whizbang in surprise. "But you know over a dozen languages...."<br />
<br />
"DOZENS." Whizbang corrected. His flipping through pages came to an end, and he peered at an open page.<br />
<br />
"...that would make that coincidence almost...."<br />
<br />
"...impossible. Aye. I know." Whizbang tapped the page. "Here. I found it. Listen to this. Sound familiar?<br />
<br />
When Hate finds love and walks the lands<br />
With enchanted dead close at hand<br />
And Mithaniel's handmaiden lays in sleep<br />
The End of All has a promise to keep.<br />
<br />
See the players here? Hate walking the lands..."<br />
<br />
"Me." River replied.<br />
<br />
"Aye." Whizbang nodded. "Then this....enchanted dead...."<br />
<br />
"Roughly translated into 'a dead enchanter.'" Vven supplied.<br />
<br />
Again a nod from Whizbang.<br />
<br />
"And Mithaniel's handmaiden laying in sleep...Camille." Pedi finished. "I'm getting goosebumps."<br />
<br />
"Prepare for goosebumps on top of goosebumps, woman." Whizbang warned, and continued on:<br />
<br />
"The grounds in one moon will crack and split<br />
And all known cities slip into the Pit.<br />
Norrath will light with unnatural flame<br />
As begins the process known as End Game.<br />
<br />
All living will die, all growing decay<br />
All that was created will wither away<br />
And how it began it will all fade away.<br />
Thus will occur on Judgement Day."<br />
<br />
River swallowed hard. "In one moon. A month. All this that happened with me. My death, Innoruuk's lessons, Camille put to sleep, even Vven dying....all of this, is going to cause the end of everything within a month?"<br />
<br />
"So it seems, according to this, and its accuracy so far leaves me little doubt that we are reading what WILL come." Whizbang mopped some sweat from his forehead with a sleeve. "Do I think you caused it to be? No, I don't think you had any choice in this. This was put into motion at the beginning of time. But are you the catalyst? Aye, River, you most certainly are."<br />
<br />
"There's more, gnome." Vven said, looking over Whizbang's shoulder. "What else does it say?"<br />
<br />
"The first was the bad news." Whiz said, "Now here....here is the good news:<br />
<br />
The only hope to deny that fate<br />
is to be championed by mortal Hate.<br />
To reverse it, Hate must pass a test.<br />
A test that is part journey, part quest."<br />
<br />
"Mortal Hate." River said. "Me again. I can fix this, with a quest." He sighed deeply. "Why does it seem I am forever doing quests? Forever quests..."<br />
<br />
"And now, "Whizbang said, "We get to the quest:<br />
<br />
Only when Fear can overcome fear, <br />
And a Nightmare shed a single tear<br />
And that tear does burn in Natural flame<br />
Can one stop the beginning of End Game.<br />
<br />
A sacrifice pure of mortal life<br />
When War finds peace from eternal strife<br />
And Love denied will even the score.<br />
Then all will be as it was Before."<br />
<br />
"Welllllll." Vven said. "Doesn't this seem easy."<br />
<br />
"It makes no sense, Whiz." River said in frustration. "When Fear can overcome fear? Love denied? Riddles? Do you understand any of this?"<br />
<br />
"Not yet," Whiz replied, "But I didn't understand the first part either until you told me your story. Give me a little time and we can..."<br />
<br />
Suddenly, from upstairs and outside, alarms began to sound from far off. The Gnomish Public Warning System, blaring its horns. In the distance, screams of women and children were heard. and then suddenly, to punctuate it, an awful banging on Whizbang's door upstairs. The ceiling creaked from the pounding, and several books slipped off the shelves to thump to the floor.<br />
<br />
"Damnation, what NOW?" Whizbang exclaimed.<br />
<br />
It was answered by one deafening word from upstairs outside his door.<br />
<br />
"OGGA!"<br />
 <br /></font></p>
	
