	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85247"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> "Um, Boss, Innoruuk is here." Fright said from within the room he disappeared into.<br />
<br />
"He is?" came a small, high pitched little voice. "Thank Us he's here! I heard he was dead! Send him in send him in!"<br />
<br />
Fright poked out his massive head. "He'll see you, Innoruuk."<br />
<br />
"Thanks." River said, not correcting him. He led the five into the room, brushing past Fright.<br />
<br />
And almost screamed.<br />
<br />
A huge lumbering behemoth of a creature was rushing towards him, made up of earth, mud, twisted roots, vines like veins running across its body, moving at a dizzying speed at him with its massive maw agape. Just looking at it almost drove River to insanity. Listening to the sharp intake of breath behind him he imagined the others were likewise terrified out of their wits.<br />
<br />
Cazic-Thule was rushing at them.<br />
<br />
And speaking.<br />
<br />
"Thank you thank you thank you Innoruuk!" it cried in that high pitched girl's voice. "I have been so worried that I was in this alon...." Suddenly, for all its tremendous weight, it screeched to a halt, took one good look at them, and screamed like a woman. Cazic dove behind Fright and peeked out over his shoulder.<br />
<br />
"Oh My Us! Who the Hells are you??" he cried, trembling.<br />
<br />
Vven burst out laughing.<br />
<br />
"Innoruuk is dead, Cazic." River said, stepping forward, shooting Vven a dirty look that almost silenced him, but not quite. "I am the new Prince of Hate."<br />
<br />
"Oh my, I was afraid of that!" Cazic said, shaking. "I heard Innoruuk was killed, but I didn't want to believe it! If Innoruuk could be slain, then how much security do any of us have? None, I say! We have none! Oh woe the day!"<br />
<br />
"I seriously don't believe this." Vven commented.<br />
<br />
"I have come..." River began, searching. "To....help you. I need to know, why are you in this state, Cazic? What has you so afraid?"<br />
<br />
"Them!" Cazic whispered from behind Fright. Fright rolled his eyes.<br />
<br />
"Who is them, Cazic?" River asked.<br />
<br />
A voice outside cut them off. "Sir, that monk is getting close to the moat again, sir."<br />
<br />
"Nonono!" Cazic wailed. "Make it go away, Fright, make it go away!"<br />
<br />
Fright sighed. "AKETHADAR!" he boomed in an earth-shattering voice. A pause and then, "Ok, Boss, I bought you some time."<br />
<br />
"He'll be back...." Cazic whispered in terror. "They always come back..."<br />
<br />
"Wait a minute wait a minute..." Vven said, a look of disbelief on his amused face. "You are afraid of PROMETHIAN ORDER? That's 'them?'"<br />
<br />
"Are they here yet??" Cazic shrieked.<br />
<br />
"Hahhah NO, but they should be, you COWARD, just to boot you out of this PLANE!" Vven mocked. "Boy, did I ever pick the right god to worship! Even if the great white hope here killed him," ...a gesture to a fuming River..."....at least I bet he didn't go down screaming like a RANGER! What is WRONG with you?? You're a god, for gods' sakes. Stand up STRAIGHT!"<br />
<br />
"DON'T HIT ME!" Cazic shrieked. Even Ramluk sighed in disgust.<br />
<br />
"Whiz," Pedi asked quietly, "Do any of your books mention Cazic being a...."<br />
<br />
"...sissy pants? No." Whizbang replied.<br />
<br />
Vven started pacing. "So aptly named, the God of Fear. I can't believe they let a creature as pitiful as you run this plane! No wonder no one ever sees you walking around outside, you're probably afraid of the fire that surrounds your own MOAT."<br />
<br />
"I wasn't always like this!" Cazic cried, chest heaving. "Just they started coming, every week, Promethian Order, with their sharp swords and wizards with fireballs and...every week. Marching in, MARCH MARCH MARCH destroying everything in their path like a swarm of locusts! A wizard epic here, an enchanter epic there, always knocking me unconscious and ripping out my brain! Do you have ANY idea how painful that is, to wake up to find your BRAIN missing?" He searched their faces for any sign of compassion.<br />
<br />
"Um, can't say I do." Whizbang tried lamely. Only Ramluk was nodding in sympathy.<br />
<br />
"Then fight BACK!" Vven exploded. "You're a GOD! Ok ok ok, how many death-touchers do you have? Fat boy over there and who else?"<br />
<br />
"Dread. He's on a coffee break." Cazic said miserably.<br />
<br />
"He's ALWAYS on a coffee break...." Fright grumbled.<br />
<br />
"TWO death-touchers." Vven confirmed. "And all you do is death-touch their scout, a monk. He's a trained PROFESSIONAL. It's his JOB to lead you into SUBMISSION!"<br />
<br />
"Well, he's the closest one..." Fright began defensively. <br />
<br />
"Of course he's the closest, they MEAN for him to be the closest! Ok ok ok. You, Thunder Thighs, you go get your buddy Dread in here. I'm going to show your boss here how to be a god."<br />
<br />
Fright looked around a little lost, but then realizing Cazic wasn't going to order him or stop him, marched out of the room.<br />
<br />
"Ok first things first." Vven said, inspecting Cazic like a bug. "That voice."<br />
<br />
"My voice?" Cazic said meekly.<br />
<br />
"Yes, that 'I spent ten years in a Trollish Prison' voice. Gotta go."<br />
<br />
"What do you want...?" Cazic asked uncertainly. "An accent?...or something?"<br />
<br />
"DEEPER!" Vven exclaimed, "Ferocious! Terrifying!" He turned. "Ramluk!"<br />
<br />
"OGGA!" Ramluk roared.<br />
<br />
"Like THAT." Vven said. River just watched in amazement as Vven ranted. "Think like an ogre, but more terrifying! Repeat after Ramluk! 'You will not evade me!'"<br />
<br />
"YOU WILL NOT INVADE ME!" Ramluk repeated a happy growl.<br />
<br />
"Please do not invade me!" Cazic squeaked. Vven sighed in disgust.<br />
<br />
"Ok ok ok work on that. Next, strategy. Now get Dread and..." Vven suddenly paused, and looked around the room. "Um, guys, could you give me and old Cazic here a few minutes alone? We need to talk, bad guy to bad guy."<br />
<br />
"Not on your life." River said.<br />
<br />
"Oh this will NEVER work!" Cazic said, throwing up his hands in despair. And then....he started crying. Big wracking sobs.<br />
<br />
"I don't HAVE a life!" Vven hissed. "And neither do any of you, unless we fulfill this quest and have Fear overcome fear. So CUT ME SOME SLACK!"<br />
<br />
River stared at Vven for a long hard time. "Ok, Vven." he said finally. "All you." And he motioned for Whiz, Ram and Pedi to follow him out to the waiting area, where they waited.<br />
<br />
And waited.<br />
<br />
And waited.<br />
<br />
"AKETHADAR!" Fright bellowed from across the land.<br />
<br />
And waited.<br />
<br />
Then, after what seemed an eternity, they heard a small tittering coming from the room. Cazic presumably.<br />
<br />
"LAUGH LIKE A GOD!" Vven bellowed, but you could hear triumph in his voice.<br />
<br />
And then the titter deepened in pitch, into a chortle, and grew, insanely in volume.<br />
<br />
Vven came out of the room, with a smug look on his face. "Let's go back to the Promethian camp, shall we?" he said. "My job here is done."<br />
<br />
"What did you do?" River said, following Vven with his crew in tow as Vven stepped out of the pyramid.<br />
<br />
"I taught him all about fear." Vven said replied nonchalantly. "Let's get to that camp, you won't want to miss this. But I guaruntee you, this part of the quest is done. That boy doesn't fear ANYTHING anymore."<br />
<br />
And ringing in the halls of the pyramid, the deep malevolent insane laughter confirmed that it was true.<br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
Aamedor looked at them with a sad smile. "Decided it wasn't worth it, huh?"<br />
<br />
"For once you used your head, Wyldechylde." Akethadar sneered, seeing the five trudge back to his camp. "Leave Cazic to the professionals."<br />
<br />
"We're done with Cazic." Riverdane said evenly. "Just wanted to warn you he may be..."<br />
<br />
"You're done with Cazic?" Akethadar laughed. "What did you go there to do? Take notes for your next wipe?"<br />
<br />
"Actually..." River began,<br />
<br />
"Yeah." Vven said, cutting River off. "That's exactly what we did. Um, Whiz, you may want to prep for a gate outta here."<br />
<br />
Whizbang looked at Vven for a moment, and after meeting the enchanter's eyes, sat down immediately and started to recall the words to one of his portal spells.<br />
<br />
"Good idea Whiz." Akethadar agreed. "Port these losers out of here. And honestly, I thought Walkers on a higher teir than these amateurs. You really should watch what company you keep, gnome." Whizbang frowned, but continued to prepare his spell.<br />
<br />
"Vven, what did I need to come here to see?" River mumbled angrily. "Promethian Order's raid leader throwing yet another slew of insults?"<br />
<br />
"You'lllll seeee." Vven singsonged softly.<br />
<br />
"ALRIGHT GUYS." Akethadar boomed, "I'M GOING TO START PULLING THE GORGOLOSKS IN A SECOND. BE READY TO...."<br />
<br />
"AAMEDOR!" a deafening voice shouted from the north. Aamedor stiffened suddenly, and tipped over on his side, face the gray ash of the dead.<br />
<br />
"You see," Vven explained with a smile. "I explained why wait for them to come to your door, to identify whom to deathtouch, when I had the names of their healer...."<br />
<br />
"TREMAS!" boomed another voice to the south. Tremas went rigid like a board, eyes wide in shock, and pitched straight forward, dead.<br />
<br />
"...and their porter?" Vven continued happily.<br />
<br />
Akethadar and Pron exchanged looks as Whizbang's chanting grew faster in speed.<br />
<br />
"Wyldechylde, what have you done?" Akethadar began. "If you meddled with..."<br />
<br />
"YOU WILL NOT INVADE ME, PRON!" came the loudest voice of them all, sounding like a thunderclap going off in a stormy sky. Pron suddenly winked out of sight, vanishing into thin air. And then the horrid sound of an ogre screaming somewhere in the distance.<br />
<br />
"Close, big guy, close. EVADE." Vven sighed to himself.<br />
<br />
Riverdane stared at Vven in horror. "You just massacred them..."<br />
<br />
Akethadar had thrown himself to the ground and was laying very very still, the defensive position of a monk feigning death to avoid notice.<br />
<br />
"Nah..." Vven said. "Promethian Order has more clerics than the Temple of Marr. They'll have this recovered in an hour. But for now, our blubbering God of Chicken now has his confidence back."<br />
<br />
Riverdane shot Vven a venemous look and then turned his attention back to Akethadar. <br />
<br />
"Ake," he offered urgently. "We still have room, port out of here with us, before...."<br />
<br />
"I wouldn't port anwhere with you, Wyldechylde." Akethadar replied, his voice full of hate. "You screwed up again and meddled in the business of Promethian Order."<br />
<br />
"Oh don't be an ass." Vven said. "He's giving you a chance to..."<br />
<br />
"You'll pay for this, River." Akethadar swore. "If it's the last thing I do, I'll have your guild destroyed."<br />
<br />
"Akethadar...." River tried again.<br />
<br />
"Ok." Vven cut in. "Have it your way." He turned and cupped his hands to his mouth.<br />
<br />
"HEY CAZIC!" he shouted, "You know that monk that was giving you that trouble?"<br />
<br />
"Go now Whiz, hurry." River said.<br />
<br />
"Going." Whizbang said. "Hold onto your seats!" And they began to shimmer from view.<br />
<br />
"HE'S FAKING!" Vven finished with a smile.<br />
<br />
And they were gone. <br /></font></p>
	
