	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85249"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> "Damnation, you idiotic inky, you must have a brain! Have you ever ONCE thought about USING IT?" Whizbang swore.<br />
<br />
"You can't possibly be talking about me." Vven replied, honestly looking around to see if another Teir'Dal was nearby. All he saw was Ramluk looking confused, Pedi looking concerned, and Riverdane looking....dangerous.<br />
<br />
"Do you see any other half-baked, sociopathic, hang-out-with-me-and-screw-up-your-life dark elves around?" Whizbang exploded.<br />
<br />
Vven looked miffed. "WHAT IS YOUR POINT?" he replied testily.<br />
<br />
"His point, Vven." Riverdane said in a low growl. "Is that you just murdered four members of Promethian Order. And you were right, they have enough clerics and force to go back in concentrated, whether Cazic is no longer afraid of them or not. And they will rez Akethadar and his boys, and they WILL remember who trained them. And due to your little trick, you have put both Razor's Edge and Walkers in a very serious political dilemma."<br />
<br />
"Oh, is that it?" Vven said casually. "I'm from Black Reign. We don't believe in politics. We live for this crap."<br />
<br />
"And we DIE from this crap!" Whizbang fumed, the top of his bald head going red.<br />
<br />
"Whizbang, relax before you icecomet your foot off!" Pedi commanded. Then she looked at Vven. "That was very irresponsible, Vven. You have put our and River's guilds in great danger."<br />
<br />
"Look, I was doing what was necessary, ok?" Vven cried out defensively. "I just want my damned body back! And if Cazic didn't get over his cold feet, there isn't going to BE any guilds or politics in a month! My methods may not be to the liking of you goody two-shoes but they WORKED! So bitch AFTER I save the world, ok?"<br />
<br />
All the anger went out of River like steam from a kettle. "Vven, for now on, talk to me first before you pull any more stunts like that. I thank you for helping us get past the first part of the quest, but you may have damned us anyway even if we do fix this. So no more surprises, ok?"<br />
<br />
"River, are you mad?" Whizbang said. "This dark elf is going to..."<br />
<br />
"Hehh hehh, 'He faking it." Hehh. That funny." Ramluk suddenly said.<br />
<br />
They all went dead quiet, looking at the chuckling ogre.<br />
<br />
"Faking. Heh." Ramluk said again.<br />
<br />
Pedi was the first to crack a smile. "Brell help me, but that was rather amusing. The look on Akethadar's face..."<br />
<br />
And she and River burst out laughing.<br />
<br />
"Damnation!" Whizbang muttered.<br />
<br />
River got control over himself, and looked around for the first time. "Whiz, where are we?"<br />
<br />
"Plane of Knowledge." Whizbang said. "Starting point for the next part of our journey. Have any of you been here before, besides Pedi?"<br />
<br />
Vven shook his head. As did River. Ramluk just looked confused. He pointed. <br />
<br />
"OGGA!" he said.<br />
<br />
And where he pointed, an ogre stood chatting with an armored high elf female. Then, through an arch in the impressive looking walls, a dark elf came marching through, turned to the high elven woman, and saluted crisply. Then the dark elf marched on past them, towards River and crew on the grass.<br />
<br />
"Fine day we're having!" the dark elf said exuberantly.<br />
<br />
"You saluted a high elf." Vven said in shock.<br />
<br />
"Yes!" the dark elf said. "I always salute my high officers!"<br />
<br />
"I'm going to be sick." Vven said miserably.<br />
<br />
"In the Plane of Knowledge," Whizbang said to Vven with an evil grin. "All races put down their natural animosity and live together in the peaceful search for knowledge. It's quite a wonder. In this tiny plane, one can find trolls shaking hands with dwarves, and iksar studying with wood elves."<br />
<br />
"It's a small world, after all!" the dark elf agreed. Vven gaped.<br />
<br />
"Well, if you'll excuse me, I'm off to see my betrothed." the dark elf said, saluting them. "You've never seen a prettier halfling lady!" And with that, he was off.<br />
<br />
"He's marrying an assling." Vven said in disgust.<br />
<br />
"Whiz," River asked. "Why here? Where are we going?"<br />
<br />
"Recall the prophecy." Whizbang said.<br />
<br />
"...'And a Nightmare shed a single tear'..." Vven said automatically.<br />
<br />
"Aye, Nightmare." Whizbang repeated.<br />
<br />
"So that means we're going to..." Pedi began.<br />
<br />
"...the Plane of Nightmares." Whizbang finished. "We're going to see Terris Thule."  <br /></font></p>
	
