<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85251"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> A match touches itself to the end of a cigarette...spark of light dimly illuminating the muck covered wall...<br />
<br />
....inhale....<br />
<br />
"It still in there?" Riverdane Wyldechylde asks, smoke curling from his fingertips. A long time ago he would be worried the smell of it would alert the inhabitants of Lower Guk, but hundreds of battles later he knows undead don't smell anything.<br />
<br />
"Aye," Bwael Kyorlean replies, closer to the entrance to the torture chamber of the undead frogs....his finger runs a trail through thick dust..."It's been in there unmoving for a long time...a long time"<br />
<br />
"If that dust is undisturbed, its friends are in there too, then. " Nizzre Kyorlean, Bwael's brother replied. How different they looked, Nizzre in his plate and Bwael in his chain and leather. Yet there were times River would swear they were the same person, thinking with the same mind, that's how fluidly they worked together.<br />
<br />
"Yes." Bwael said, "The ones I tracked to this room last week are still here....the undead are funny, they just stand in place like sentinels, not moving for weeks on end."<br />
<br />
"Where's Grelin?" River asks. "Can we take on this bastard without a healer?"<br />
<br />
"Grelin's still coming." Nizzre said. <br />
<br />
"Grrrreat." River replied, "We have twenty minutes before he gets here..." He sighs impatiently. "We have to do this now, before these frogs get wind of what we did to the previous guards"<br />
<br />
"I'll heal..." Camille Wyldechylde, River's beautiful blonde wife says. She smiles winningly, and something in River's heart aches. "I won't let you die."<br />
<br />
"You never do, baby, you never do..." He looks over at Bwael and Nizzre. "You want to risk it?"<br />
<br />
Bwael looks at Nizzre. "I'll snare?"<br />
<br />
Nizzre nods, "I'll root."<br />
<br />
River smiles. "No way to yank this one clean, the room's too small."<br />
<br />
Bwael draws a wicked blade. "Bring it."<br />
<br />
On that, three more blades whisper out of scabbards, and River makes his way around the corner.<br />
<br />
There it is...the Frenzied Ghoul, with two other frogs, one, a lesser muscled frogluk zombie, undead rotted animated remains of the proud froglok race, and the other with totally white eyes, blind and yet seeing, eminating the quiet power of a wizard. A caster of power...but River is not without power himself....<br />
<br />
His fingers stroke his moustache thoughfully, words of power spoken quietly under his breathe...then, with fingers splaying forth he murmurs "Bringing a world of pain, via Riverdane, to the Frenzied ghoul."<br />
<br />
A small nimbus of power leaps from River's fingers, shooting across the room to infuse the Frenzy. Immediately there is motion. A bolt of power flies from the wizard's webbed fingers. Only ducking behind his shield did River keep his head on his shoulders, the bolt deflecting off the polished face to explode off a close rock. And then the frogs were upon him.<br />
<br />
"Time to dance with the Frenzy!" River called over his shoulder. He flicks his cigarette to the ground and stubs it out. A pivot, a dash and River is running back to the group, to see the dead set stares of Camille, Bwael, and Nizzre,<br />
<br />
"we've got a few incoming" River says. Camille nods to him curtly. She has been here all to often before. She knows the drill.<br />
<br />
Four swords lift as one, each person pulling forth their own arcane knowledge.<br />
<br />
River's eyes are on fire as the three frogs turn the corner and decend upon them.<br />
<br />
"Do it to it...."<br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
....sheild up....<br />
<br />
.....the Frenzy is upon them....<br />
<br />
...the frogloks, all three are singular in purpose....Riverdane has woken them from their silent guard, and they have one singular thought....destroy the shadowknight...<br />
<br />
One webbed fist swing, hard enough to crack stone, to bounce off River's sheild....With the Frenzy deflected, River swings up and parries with his sword a descending blade from the Warrior, rebounding it to the side....one arm committed to the Frenzy, one to the Warrior, and River hears the sound of energybuilding up in the Wizard.<br />
<br />
"Oh Shi......stuns UP!" he cries.<br />
<br />
Nizzre and Camille nod at each other and wrinkle their brows.<br />
<br />
Blue light flies from their hands, a virtual force. The wizard is stopped dead in its tracks, blood trickling slowly from its ears and the double stun knocks it temporarily senseless.<br />
<br />
"I have the Warrior." Bwael calls out, dashing to a far corner and drawing his bow....in an instant, the arrow is knocked and flying, catching the warrior in the back of the neck. The Warrior bellows in anguish, both it and the Frenzy turning to the ranger in the corner, who has already slung his bow onto his back and has sword out, ready....<br />
<br />
The Wizard begins to blink, regaining its senses. The mumbling begins again, until Camille's sheild smashes itself into its face. "Be quiet, you." she says. It has no choice but to comply.<br />
<br />
The Frenzy and Warrior advance quickly upon Bwael. His small woodelf frame is overshadowed by the two hulking undead frogs, but he is unflinching. These four have faced far worse than this.<br />
<br />
"Come here you..." River calls out, with a gesture at the Frenzy with his sheild hand....a green nimbus, smokelike wafts out of his fingers, curling into the ears and eyes of the Frenzies head. It makes a small sound.....pain?...as the disease cloud begins to eat at its cells. It's attention turns back to River. <br />
<br />
"There we go..." River murmurs, and readies himself for this juggarnaut.<br />
<br />
The Warrior is oblivious to the loss of his companion. Narrowminded, focused and bent on Bwael's destruction, it advances another foot.<br />
<br />
"Rooting the Warrior." Nizzre calls out. Camille nods, hacking her sword into the Wizard's shoulder. Black blood sprays across the wall and onto her armor. Hmm, I'll have to clean that off later, she thinks. Might stain.<br />
<br />
Nizzre's fingers twitch in the direction of the warrior. Suddenly thick brownish roots spring from the floor, an articifial substance drawn from the very floor itself. They quickly wrap the ankles and legs of the Warrior, holding it down to the ground. It blinks lids over eyeless holes in surprise.....focus on Bwael lost, it begins to hack at the roots with it's sword.....Bwael hugs the wall tight to join Camille and Nizzre, and the butchering of the hapless Wizard continues, this time, three swords instead of one.<br />
<br />
River swings up his sword at the Frenzy, as another green black arm descends upon him......connection, and the swing should have cut off the Frenzy's arm.....instead, it sinks perhaps half an inch in....The Frenzy bellows in pain, as River yanks the blade free.<br />
<br />
Half an inch...<br />
<br />
Oh boy...<br />
<br />
And then River discovers why the Frenzy is called the Frenzy...<br />
<br />
A black cord cinched around the frogs "waist" begins to glow and hum with a force all of its own.....and suddenly the Frenzy's webbed claws are flying in a flurry of attack, River barely able to follow their movement.<br />
<br />
Connection to his chest, air knocked completely out of his lungs.<br />
<br />
"Ohhh, that's going to leave a mark" he sputters, trying to get his breath.<br />
<br />
Another connection into his chest plate. And a loud crack. Black spots before his eyes. <br />
<br />
"Yup." River says, as unconsciousness begins to steal over him. "That was a rib." He stumbles, attempting to stand upright, but light and coordination is beginning to steal away from him.<br />
<br />
The Wizard is little more than a throbbing pile of severed flesh, Camille, Nizzre and Bwael slicing it repeatedly, as it continues in the amazing way of the undead to fight....Camille senses rather than hears River faltering....Her sword continues to slice,as she turns her head in River's direction...to see him slipping to the ground...<br />
<br />
Her eyes light preternaturally blue, aglow with light...<br />
<br />
"Heal..." she whispers... <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
.....light....<br />
<br />
....bright blue light.....a supernova under closed lids...<br />
<br />
....and Riverdane draws himself erect, ribs mended, bruise there but body healed....<br />
<br />
"Thank you baby." he tells Camille, spitting at the webbed feet of the Frenzy.<br />
<br />
"You're welcome, baby." she replies, as she beams a smile at him and lops the wizard'd right hand from its wrist. Bwael and Nizzre stop a moment to exchange a look. Nizzre rolls his eyes.<br />
<br />
The Frenzy gives pause, a moment...a dangerous moment. River sees the opening, and lunges with his sword. The Frenzy is a trained warrior, turns sideways, smacking the blade away from where it was aiming to skewer his body. Exactly the move River has anticipated.<br />
<br />
The tip of River's sword snags the belt cinched around the froglok. With a quick twist of his wrist, River slices it in two and flips it up in the air in a high lazy arc.<br />
<br />
"Inc flowing black silk sash" River calls out, bringing his armored knee up into the Frenzy's belly. Crunch, and crippling pain shoots through River's knee. Next time use weapons, River, he thinks. Monk you're not.<br />
<br />
Bwael's free hand reaches over his head mid-swing at the wizard's side, grabbing the flying belt. He tucks it into his pocket. "Nice ghetto pick pocket, Riv..." he says, chopping a huge chunk of decaying flesh from the wizard.<br />
<br />
"And ghetto slow...." River laughs, pushing the Frenzy back violently with his sheild. Another splatter of blood splashes across his face from their direction. He looks over, and tries to make out what reason they may have for beating the misshappened quivering mass of frog flesh before them.<br />
<br />
"It's dead, guys." Another spray of blood. "Trust me, it's very very dead."<br />
<br />
And STARS as the Frenzy connects to the side of his head.<br />
<br />
River staggers to the side, spots again before his eyes. He spins against the wall blinded momentarily.<br />
<br />
"Aye." he hears Nizzre say. "It's dead." And then more butchering, closer. Steel hitting stone, by the sound of it. They are upon the Frenzy.<br />
<br />
"You ok?" he hears Camille ask, his eyes still blurred.<br />
<br />
"I'm good I'm good..." He replies shakily....he knows how every heal takes a little more out of her, till she has nothing left to give. His sword raises shakily, blood trickling down the side of his face. Concentrate River. He hears a sharp sound of pain. Camille caught the aggro, the Frenzy was upon her, somewhere to his left. Reflex and his hand flays out two fingers separate and cross, and a wave of power pushes out in the direction of the battle. Come on you bastard taunt....two fingers splayed and crossed was his most powerful taun...wait a minute. He shakes his head again to clear the cobwebs, and wipes blood from his eyes. Cross the fingers after, or before...?...hmmm<br />
<br />
"Riv..." Bwael says dryly, chopping at the Frenzy's back. "You just feared the warrior."<br />
<br />
Nizzre has stopped fighting. Camille has stopped fighting. Even the Frenzy seems to have stopped, in his blurred vision, to gape at him.<br />
<br />
"And Root just broke." Nizzre finishes.<br />
<br />
River's head snaps to the right to see the panicked Warrior disappear around the corner. His desperate eyes turn back to his three companions, who were pushing the Frenzy back and forth between them with sheilds and kicks. And then that far off sound. Growing louder. The sound of many webbed feet hopping....getting louder.<br />
<br />
With two hands wrapped around his sword Reaver, he swings up in an arc, down, and cleaves the skull of the Frenzy in two....it drops to the ground as the four pull their swords from various spots in its now inanimate carcass. River grabs Camille urgently by the wrist.<br />
<br />
"Crazy bastard uses fear in a dungeon." Nizzre mumbles, shaking his head, sheathing his sword. Bwael has already unslung his bow and heading an opposite direction the Warrior has fled.<br />
<br />
"That way!" River calls, as if Nizzre doesn't already know...<br />
<br />
"TRAIN...!" <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
Through corridors they run, up stairs, the sound of the undead frogs deafening, a blind alley, four friends backtrack and choose the correct path, but the lead they have on their pursuers is waning.<br />
<br />
Closer, closer, a collective froaking building in pitch, another stairs, another corner and...<br />
<br />
Grelin standing in front of them, chewing on a piece of hay.<br />
<br />
"Hi guys." he says.<br />
<br />
"TRAIN!" River exclaims lifting up Grelin by the arm. Nizzre grabs the other, and they carry Grelin backward, his feet a foot above the ground. The half-elf's feet dangle uselessly.<br />
<br />
"Um, evac?" he offers.<br />
<br />
"Good idea." Bwael comments, turning around to run backwards, firing lightning fast into the green tide about to sweep them over.<br />
<br />
A few words in broken Elven, and the druid Grelin's eyes light green, and with a wink, stopping the frogs dead in their tracks, they are gone.<br />
<br />
POOF.<br />
<br />
A grassy gnoll, next to strange druidic statues. The druid ring in Southern Desert of Ro. They are panting, the sounds of their gasps loud in the relative quiet of SoRo.<br />
<br />
"Nice timing, Grel." River remarks, waking toward wear the grass ends and the dunes of sand begins.<br />
<br />
"That was fun!" Camille says, eyes sparkling, joining her husband as he sits down on a hill of sand and begins stripping off his armor. She removes the plate pieces from her sweat-drenched armor one by one, and Nizzre also removes his battle gear in favor of the light, everyday clothing they wore underneathe. Bwael is counting his arrows in his quiver. Grelin, as usual, is just sitting on his haunches, chewing on that piece of hay, watching them quietly.<br />
<br />
"You know," River says. "We do some pretty impressive stuff, considering the gear we have. This black silk sash should help outfit us a little better. No cleric, no chanter, but we still lived."<br />
<br />
"Thanks to Grelin." Bwael adds. Grelin just chews.<br />
<br />
"You want good gear, join Promethian Order." Nizzre says. "I saw a few of them the other day up close. Those guys are geared to the teeth."<br />
<br />
"Not my style," River says laying back on the sand and popping a fresh cigarette into his mouth. He lights and inhales deeply. "Their requirements are too military for me, and I need my downtime. Plus, I don't take orders very well..."<br />
<br />
"We know." Bwael and Nizzre say in uncanny unison.<br />
<br />
"You know, WE could start a guild..." River muses.<br />
<br />
Camille crawls across River's prone body and rests her head against his chest as he gazes up at the clouds. "Silly." she says, "What do you want to make a guild for? The five of us do just fine."<br />
<br />
"Baby, there's other things out there I want to see, you know. I'm tired of Guk." His eyes have a faraway look.<br />
<br />
"Riv, you DO know a ton of people. I bet you could find some more to join." Nizzre contemplates.<br />
<br />
"I need to get more sun." Bwael says, "Guk is getting old."<br />
<br />
"A guild, a guild." River repeats. "But what would we call it? We don't suck, we're rather good at what we do, and we operate well under pressure. We like danger and high pressure, dancing along the razor's edge."<br />
<br />
"That's it, there's our name." Grelin says suddenly. The other four turn and stare at him. Grelin rarely ever speaks.<br />
<br />
"What's our name?" River asks.<br />
<br />
Grelin chews on his piece of hay and smiles. "...'We Don't Suck.'...." <br /></font></p>
	
	<p></p>
