<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85252"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> ~~wake~~<br />
<br />
River's eyes snapped open, as he saw his friends and Terris staring at him. Out of the corner of his eyes, he saw the images of Camille, Grelin, Nizzre and Bwael wisp away like smoke. His recollection of the past, his dream, was physical for all to see. He felt violated in some abstract way. They were his memories.<br />
<br />
"Should have stayed with 'We don't suck'." Vven commented.<br />
<br />
Terris' face was impassive. ~~even as a god, you dream of war, conquest~men are so predictable~show me the woman~<br />
<br />
River tried to resist her command, but found himself impotent against her will.<br />
<br />
~~sleep~~ <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
Smoke wafts upward before his eyes, the acrid clouds stinging his eyes, as he glances down at the task before him.<br />
<br />
One blue vellium boot, taken from a fallen dorf in Icewell, slips onto a foot.<br />
<br />
Camille's eyes are on his back, those twin blue beacons....she watches him silently putting on his armor, knowing once more he is leaving their home...a sharpening stone hones the edge of her sword, yet not a sound leaves her lips, as she watches her man preparing.<br />
<br />
Another blue boot, heavy armor, weighing down his every step....a flick of his cigarette, ash falls into a pottered bowl.<br />
<br />
A knock on the door. Camille's eyes register on it, sharpening stone working the blade, working the blade.<br />
<br />
"Come in." he says, lifting greaves off their hook on the wall....the guardian armor, silver and shining, clinks together as he begins to snap in place the buckles and ties to hold it together over his tanned leggings.<br />
<br />
A reptilian head pokes its way into the room. Zullie, one of his officers, looks through serpentine eyes at Camille and him as he snaps the last buckle into place and straightens himself.<br />
<br />
"Just the daily news." Zullie informs him. "Is now a good time, or...?" She lets the question hang pregnant in the air.<br />
<br />
"Aye." he says, fitting the black umbral tunic over his torso. A gift from the time he had successfully walked the Plane of Fear....taken without permission from its owner. Vambracers followed, the same hard heavy metal. Camille's stone works the blade, works the blade.<br />
<br />
"Well, several members left, and word is several more planning to." Zullie begins.<br />
<br />
"Expected...I am rarely surprised." Shoulder pieces set and locked, another tap of ash.<br />
<br />
"Also applications from about a dozen people, Nizzre gave them to me this morning." She waved several pieces in front of him.<br />
<br />
"Please, Zullie, on that pile over there." With one hand being slipped into a guardian bracer, he gestures to a growing pile. "Let's hope these applicants know what they are signing onto." The bracer seemed heavier, this afternoon....all of his armor seemed heavier.<br />
<br />
"The Alliance is doing well, but they want to know when another Fear raid will be planned, and Kedge Keep, and an assault on the Plane of Growth....and of course Temple of Veeshan" Zullie checked off her list matter of factly.<br />
<br />
Another bracer locked into place. Reaching for his blood ember gauntlets, lying on the table. "All those raids, do they have leaders yet?"<br />
<br />
Zullie blinks heavy lids and looks at him. "No, just talk, I think they are waiting for you to lead."<br />
<br />
He glances over at Camille, but she is intent on her weapon, working the edge, working the edge.<br />
<br />
"Also with the momentum gained from our recent Epic successes, folks are wondering why you aren't focusing on cleric epics, wizard, and bard...or warrior, or.."<br />
<br />
"When I can get to them Zullie" he says, too short for his own liking. His gloves slip on as Zullie flinches.<br />
<br />
She seems reluctant to go on. "Also, the younger folks want more lower geared raids, to train on, they think you focus too much on the more experienced members..."<br />
<br />
"I've begun that...." he says, looking at the helm on the wall...he rarely uses one, not liking the way it confines him. But today, he wants to hide from the world...he stubs out the cigarette and lifts it over his head.<br />
<br />
"Tell them all I am working it....all of it." he says, dropping the helm over his head. A sharp cry from Camille, short. The sharpening stone lays split in two on the floor, her hand bleeding bright red drops. <br />
<br />
"Very well." Zullie says, backing toward the door.<br />
<br />
He remember when it was simpler, when the only responsibility he had was to his wife and three companions. Since then he had helped build an empire, and with it, came change. With a silent groan, he lifts his armored body to full stature....Camille has healed her hand already, and finally looks at him. Those beautiful eyes lock on his. But they are older now, those eyes. And they look tired.<br />
<br />
Zullie bumps into Nizzre coming through the door. He moves to accomodate her, and glaces at him.<br />
<br />
"River, they're waiting for you." he says.<br />
<br />
He takes his sword Reaver from its place on the wall, not looking at anyone anymore.<br />
<br />
A whisper.<br />
<br />
"I'm coming" <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
~~wake~~<br />
<br />
Riverdane's eyes flew open. Terris was standing above him, disdain in her eyes.<br />
<br />
~~what of her?~~ Terris' voice floated down, judging him in tone and finding him lacking. ~~she bled for you, bled BECAUSE of you, and yet, you left her~~ Her eyes held the accusation, and River could not meet them. Her voice grew thick with scorn. ~~what did she ever see in you, riverdane wyldechylde, son of innoruuk?~~<br />
<br />
'That's what we're ALL trying to figure out." Vven muttered.<br />
<br />
~~SILENCE, THING OF DREAMS!~~ she bellowed, the volume of her voice literally pushing Vven back. His lower lip trembled in fear. ~~you share the same wicked sex as he~speak again and it shall be the last words uttered from your cursed lips~~<br />
<br />
Vven, eyes wide, made a gesture across his lips as if locking them shut and then promptly throwing away the key.<br />
<br />
Pedi took a tentitive step foreward, gripping Whizbang's arm unconsciously and dragging the trembling gnome forward quite against his will.<br />
<br />
"Why, Terris?" she asked softly. "Why do you hate men so much?"<br />
<br />
Terris fixed her glare upon the small woman. ~~you will learn~~ she said with a nod, gesturing with one long wraith-like finger at Whizbang. ~~did he tell you he loved you?~did he pledge his soul to you~what lies did he whisper in your ear as you lay panting upon sweaty sheets in the dark?~ Whizbang's face, top of his bald head, and prominent ears all flushed a deep red.<br />
<br />
"Yes," Pedi said, gathering courage. "My Whizbang loves me."<br />
<br />
~~he lies~~ Terris replied cooly. ~~all men lie~they tell you what they must to part your legs, and then, eventually, they part your company, leaving you with a broken maidenhood and a broken heart~~<br />
<br />
"Whizbang has never lied to m..." Pedi began earnestly.<br />
<br />
~~ALL THINGS MALE LIE!~~ she thundered. Then her voice dropped in volume. ~~do you find it odd?~that i have no mouth?~~ She regarded Pedi, waiting for an answer. When she received none, she continued on. ~~i removed my own mouth, as if it never existed, after telling a male that I loved him~he lied to me, and when he left me alone, i vowed i would never speak of feelings of love to a man ever again~~<br />
<br />
Pedi's eyes were huge, as she stared up at the goddess before her. "You loved a man, and he left you, and when he did you removed your own mouth?"<br />
<br />
~~not a mere man~~ Terris murmured, her voice far away. ~~a god~he took my heart in his powerful hands, and made me a woman while whispering the tenderest song to fall from any man's lips that walk the heavens or hells~and made more powerful by the sheer opposite he was of a tender man~rallos zek, god of war, took my innocence in his stride~but where i thought i met him on a field of white lilies, he saw it as just another battlefield, with me a war to be won~and win he did, i loved him and begged before i opened myself to him that he would never leave me~and he agreed, and i, fool that i was, believed him~and when he had had his way with me, he marched off to yet another war~and never came back~~ She blinked slowly, lost in the memory, and then slowly opened her eyes.<br />
<br />
~~he never...came...back~~<br />
<br />
A single teardrop, as silver as the moon, glimmered in the corner of one eye, and then, dropping in slow motion, fell.<br />
<br />
Pedi cupped her hand, the tear falling into it, frozen in its shape, not cold like ice, nor hot as salty tears are, just a solid, pearlescent reminder of a goddess' sorrow. She held it as if it were a living thing.<br />
<br />
~~for you i cry~~ Terris said to Pedi. ~~and for camille, that she may live~~ Pedi regarded the solemn woman with her own eyes brimming with tears. ~~and for me~~ Terris finished quietly, ~~i cry for me~~<br />
<br />
Terris turned her swanlike neck to River, and her eyes were cold once more.<br />
<br />
~~begone, riverdane wyldechylde, son of innoruuk~~ she commanded. ~~wake mithaniel's handmaiden, lest i cry in vain~~<br />
<br />
And with that, she shimmered from view, her two luminous black eyes the last thing to vanish into the perpetual night. <br />
 <br /></font></p>
	
