<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post85255"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Riverdane</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Guest</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: <br>
	Guild: <br>
	<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Profile</a><br>
	</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br /> "Let him rot." Whizbang said. Pedi punched him hard in the shoulder.<br />
<br />
"Ow! Damnation, woman!" Whizbang exclaimed, rubbing his shoulder. "That evil bastard was more trouble than he was worth!"<br />
<br />
"Regardless," Riverdane said, leading Brimstone toward the portal stone to the Plane of Tranquility. "You heard Terris. Vven is vital to the success of this quest."<br />
<br />
"Yeah, I heard her." Whizbang grumbled, reluctantly falling into step behind Pedi and Ramluk. "She also mentioned something about male reproductive organs roasting on a spit."<br />
<br />
They touched the portal stone, and were gone. <br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
"He looks so....lonely." Pedi commented quietly, peering through the bars.<br />
<br />
Vven sat on the edge of a cot, a piece of chalk in his hand, scrawling something on the walls. Next to the bed was a platter of mouldy bread and an empty cup. Vven was scratching out his writings over a foul smelling hole in the stone floor. Most likely the toilet in his drab prison. He was writing in Common tongue, large letters River could make out from outside the cell:<br />
<br />
-Here I sit, a lonely inky,<br />
Oh! I just left a stinky!-<br />
<br />
"I see you have your body back, if you're holding that chalk." River said, snapping Vven's head around in surprise.<br />
<br />
"No." Vven said miserably. "Just in here I am solid, to prevent me from passing through the bars. Took you long enough, I've been in here ten minutes. Some friends you are."<br />
<br />
"I'm leaving." Whizbang said abruptly. Pedi stepped on his foot. Hard. Whizbang choked back a cry.<br />
<br />
"I've been spending my time rotting here reading a few bits of enlightenment from past prisoners." Vven went on. "Seems some of Norrath's more nortorious criminals have spent some time in this cell." He pointed to the wall at something written in Iksar. "Like this, 'Saalron was here, 3712'."<br />
<br />
"Somehow, you occupying the room of former sociopaths doesn't surprise me, Vven." Whiz said dryly, stepping to the side reflexively to avoid Pedi's jab to his ribs.<br />
<br />
"Here's one of my favorites." Vven continued, pointing to another set of scribbles. <br />
<br />
-There once was a woman from Halas<br />
Who used fireball wands as a phallus<br />
They found her left breast<br />
In the Estate of Unrest<br />
And half of her-"<br />
<br />
"Soooo, how are we getting you out of here, Vven?" Riverdane interrupted.<br />
<br />
"I have no idea." Vven said forlornly, slumping onto the cot. "They haven't even told me what charges I am imprisoned for."<br />
<br />
"They're probably still reading the LIST." Whizbang snapped.<br />
<br />
"Back OFF, gnome." Vven growled. "Before I reach through these bars and ADD to that list!"<br />
<br />
"Enough!" Riverdane sighed. "Whiz, how do we get him out?"<br />
<br />
Whizbang didn't look happy giving the information, but after a glare from his wife decided it was in his best interest to divulge. "We need to take his case before the Tribunal. They may grant us audience to clear his name...in the odd chance that he didn't do whatever they think he did."<br />
<br />
"Alright, Vven, sit tight." River said, then turned to Whizbang.<br />
<br />
"Lead the way."<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
   ***   ***   ***<br />
<br />
<br />
Surrounded.<br />
<br />
Riverdane's stomach heaved as he glanced down at his feet. Standing in the trial room of the Plane of Justice, the large stone slab he stood on would suddenly disappear, leaving him on solid ground, but standing in empty space, floating seemingly in thin air. Ramluk growled next to him, also thrown off by the sudden change in perspective. Whizbang and Pedi shifted uneasily, one moment firmly planted on the ground, the next, suspended in a night sky with stars and suns dotting the background, above them, below them. And around them, six huge robed figures staring silently at them, was the Tribunal. Each carrying a huge hammer, each no more than a living robe. But the power eminating from those robed non-beings was stronger than any physical shape could produce. River felt as if he were guilty of....something. It didn't matter what. Just feeling as if he was guilty and that they knew it, and were, with their eyeless gaze, deciding on his sentence.<br />
<br />
The first spoke, voice deep and resonant, coming from within the robes. The voice of The Law.<br />
<br />
"What..." it said.<br />
<br />
And then clockwise, each figure said but one word. River turned to face each like a top.<br />
<br />
"Do..."<br />
<br />
"You..."<br />
<br />
"Seek..."<br />
<br />
"Mortal..."<br />
<br />
"Hate...?"<br />
<br />
River swallowed his unease with difficulty and addressed the first on.<br />
<br />
"You have a companion of mine, Vven Psyphon." he said carefully. "I would like to know what charges he is being imprisoned for and how we may go about freeing him."<br />
<br />
"Bringing..."<br />
<br />
"Forth..."<br />
<br />
"The..."<br />
<br />
"Prisoner..."<br />
<br />
"Vven..."<br />
<br />
"Psyphon..."<br />
<br />
On the last word, Vven appeared in a blink before them, from thin air. His hands were shackled together, as well as a short chain binding his feet. The chalk was still in his hands. He gaped.<br />
<br />
"Prisoner..."<br />
<br />
"Vven..."<br />
<br />
"Psyphon's..."<br />
<br />
"Trial..."<br />
<br />
"To..."<br />
<br />
"Commence..."<br />
<br />
"Well." Vven said testily. "Don't you guys knock first? You almost caught me with my pants down. Your gourmet bread gave me the runs."<br />
<br />
"The..."<br />
<br />
"Prisoner..."<br />
<br />
"Will..."<br />
<br />
"Now..."<br />
<br />
"Be..."<br />
<br />
"Judged..."<br />
<br />
"What?" Vven said. "Do you guys share the same brain?"<br />
<br />
Silence.<br />
<br />
Vven opened his mouth to say more.<br />
<br />
"Vven." Whizbang said. "Shut up."<br />
<br />
And then as one, all six hammers swung down, hit empty air and the deafening sound of a gavel strike reverberated through the room.<br />
<br />
The first Tribunal spoke.<br />
<br />
"This Court is now in order."<br />
<br />
Somewhere in the distance, the sound of cell door slamming closed, and a muffled scream.  <br /></font></p>
	
